abstract: OTTAWA, Ontario, Dec. 30.--Ranchmen in the Canadian Northwest are suffering the loss of many of their cattle by attacks of wolves which infest the country in the vicinity of Pincher Creek. abstract: LOGANSPORT, Ind., Dec. 30.--For the second time in two years Kentland, Newton County, this State, was visited by a disastrous fire yesterday morning. It originated in the business section, and was not controlled until nearly every shop and storeroom had been wiped out. The loss is estimated at from $40,000 to $50,000, mostly covered by insurance. The disaster was caused by an incendiary.
